A new customer needs to configure a Doxee work center in their Sales Cloud. This article explains how to do it.

- In the Sales Cloud navigate yourself to the Administrator work center.

- Open General Settings. 

![A blue background with white text  Description automatically generated](data:image/png;base64,)

- Choose Custom Work Center.

![A screenshot of a computer  Description automatically generated](data:image/png;base64,)

- Add a new work center by clicking on plus button. As Type choose “Work Center” and enter any name you chose. 

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Now you need to configure three Work Center Views (for Query Builder, Business Designer &amp; Configuration Manager). Click on the same plus button as in the step #4. Now choose as a Type “Work Center View”. You can again choose any name freely. As Assigned Work Center choose the name that you have configured in the step #4. 

![A screenshot of a computer  Description automatically generated](data:image/png;base64,)

- As a next step you need to assign this work center to a user role. You can do it again in the General Settings in the Business Roles section. 

![A screenshot of a computer  Description automatically generated](data:image/png;base64,)

Choose the business role and click on the “Edit” button. 

![A white and blue line  Description automatically generated with medium confidence](data:image/png;base64,)

Under Work Center and View Assignments you can choose which work centers are assigned for this business role. Please choose the newly created work center and hit the “Save” button. 

![A screenshot of a computer  Description automatically generated](data:image/png;base64,)

It might take up to 24 hours for the work center to appear on the menu.

- Now you need to configure a mashup for each work center view. Open the work center view from the left side menu. 

![A screenshot of a computer  Description automatically generated](data:image/png;base64,)

Click on the user icon in the top right corner and select Start Adaptation. 

![A screenshot of a computer  Description automatically generated](data:image/png;base64,)

Click on Add button and select Mashup. 

![A screenshot of a computer  Description automatically generated](data:image/png;base64,)

Select the mashup from the menu (Infinica Query Builder for Query Builder, Infinica Business Designer for Business Designer &amp; Infinica Configuration Manager for Configuration Manager). 

![A screenshot of a computer  Description automatically generated](data:image/png;base64,)

&nbsp;

For best practice choose Full Width and Height 100%.

- Before you start using the app, you need to configure the URLs of Doxee components. This will be done in the Doxee Configuration Manager (you can now open the manager from the left side menu). The URLs will be provided to you by Doxee.

## Doxee Business Designer
To design templates, navigate to Doxee work space in the left side menu. Choose Doxee Business Designer. This will launch the Businees Designer component.

![A screenshot of a computer  Description automatically generated](data:image/png;base64,)

## Doxee Query Builder
You can map the dynamic fields in your template with CRM data objects in the Query Builder. Open Doxee work space on the left side menu and select Doxee Query Builder.

To start a new mapping, press “New query”.

![A screenshot of a computer  Description automatically generated](data:image/png;base64,)

Choose your destination.

![A screenshot of a computer  Description automatically generated](data:image/png;base64,)

Select entity.

![A screenshot of a computer  Description automatically generated](data:image/png;base64,)

Select fields:

![A screenshot of a computer  Description automatically generated](data:image/png;base64,)

Add filter or sorting (optional).

![A screenshot of a computer  Description automatically generated](data:image/png;base64,)

Give the query a name and save it. You can download the query XML pressing “Show XML structure”. This XML you can use as dynamic data sheet during template design.

To you the query in the Mashup return to the home page of Query Builder. The first column is an ID. Remember it, you will use it in the Mashup configuration.
